1
00:02:23,280 --> 00:02:25,000
Paisan Farm isn't a place to go
for an afternoon stroll.

2
00:02:25,080 --> 00:02:26,440
Well, I like breaking the rules.

3
00:02:28,040 --> 00:02:29,560
<i>He chose to come back now.</i>

4
00:02:29,640 --> 00:02:31,800
That means he must have been planning it.

5
00:02:31,880 --> 00:02:33,680
If he shows up in court
and says he's still alive,

6
00:02:33,760 --> 00:02:34,960
everything here will be a mess.

7
00:02:35,040 --> 00:02:36,320
What's that?

8
00:02:36,400 --> 00:02:40,840
A magic medicine
to free Yai from his suffering.

9
00:02:42,400 --> 00:02:44,240
- You… Teera.
- Mr. Yai.

10
00:02:44,320 --> 00:02:46,080
You poisoned me!

11
00:02:46,160 --> 00:02:47,480
- Ah!
- No. Stop!

12
00:02:47,560 --> 00:02:51,400
Oh! A whitening deodorant roll-on
that eliminates armpit odor.

13
00:02:51,480 --> 00:02:52,400
Come on, ma'am.

14
00:02:52,480 --> 00:02:55,640
I'll just by you two alum crystals
for you to dip in the water.

15
00:02:55,720 --> 00:02:57,880
Then you can smoothen the sharp edges

16
00:02:57,960 --> 00:03:00,720
with your foot
then apply it on your armpit.

17
00:03:00,800 --> 00:03:02,680
I guarantee you
the results are just as good.

18
00:03:02,760 --> 00:03:07,000
Your armpit hair will be soft and silky.

19
00:03:08,320 --> 00:03:09,600
You filthy bastard!

20
00:03:09,680 --> 00:03:10,840
You'll see.

21
00:03:11,600 --> 00:03:13,640
I'll tell Auntie to fire you!

22
00:03:33,440 --> 00:03:34,880
<i>Hey, ooh, lala</i>

23
00:03:35,920 --> 00:03:37,200
- Noi.
- Yes?

24
00:03:38,600 --> 00:03:40,240
Is Ms. Nee back?

25
00:03:40,320 --> 00:03:41,440
Oh, I don't know.

26
00:03:41,520 --> 00:03:43,240
I just went to get the clothes.

27
00:03:44,280 --> 00:03:45,440
And where's Mr. Yai?

28
00:03:46,320 --> 00:03:49,560
Maybe he's out hunting
for some stray dogs, or upstairs.

29
00:03:52,440 --> 00:03:54,960
Remember! Do not hit anyone ever again.

30
00:03:55,040 --> 00:03:56,120
This is bad.

31
00:03:56,920 --> 00:03:59,080
- Workers are people, not slaves!
- Are you crazy?!

32
00:03:59,160 --> 00:04:00,280
You lunatic!

33
00:04:02,400 --> 00:04:03,560
How dare you hit me?

34
00:04:03,640 --> 00:04:05,360
Even Auntie has never hit me before!

35
00:04:05,880 --> 00:04:08,480
Who hit you? This is called a slap!

36
00:04:08,560 --> 00:04:10,720
A hard slap so you remember!

37
00:04:12,720 --> 00:04:14,920
Ugh! Why is she so loud?!

38
00:04:19,200 --> 00:04:22,680
Let go of me, you lunatic!

39
00:04:22,760 --> 00:04:23,920
Are you crazy?!

40
00:04:24,000 --> 00:04:25,360
- Whoa!
- Mr. Yai!

41
00:04:25,440 --> 00:04:27,760
Mr. Yai, please let go of Ms. Nee. Please.

42
00:04:28,680 --> 00:04:30,080
Huh? Ms. Nee.

43
00:04:30,160 --> 00:04:31,640
Oh, Ms. Nee. Ah!

44
00:04:31,720 --> 00:04:33,160
- Ms. Nee.
- Ah!

45
00:04:33,240 --> 00:04:35,400
Pin! Why are you being nice to him?

46
00:04:35,480 --> 00:04:37,160
He's just a stupid worker.

47
00:04:37,760 --> 00:04:38,640
- Ugh.
- Ms. Nee…

48
00:04:39,240 --> 00:04:41,600
Look at his face. Look at the mess he is.

49
00:04:41,680 --> 00:04:42,560
Bleh.

50
00:04:42,640 --> 00:04:44,200
He's disgusting, nauseating.

51
00:04:44,280 --> 00:04:45,320
Bleh, bleh.

52
00:04:45,400 --> 00:04:46,400
Mr. Yai.

53
00:04:47,000 --> 00:04:50,840
Get out of here now. I'm firing you.

54
00:04:58,000 --> 00:05:00,160
- Oh…
- Huh?

55
00:05:06,960 --> 00:05:09,440
- Ah…
- What the hell is wrong with you, Noi?

56
00:05:09,520 --> 00:05:10,880
Why are you pointing like that?

57
00:05:12,720 --> 00:05:15,840
Ms. Nee. Did you know
who you were insulting?

58
00:05:24,960 --> 00:05:27,320
Mr. Yai. Mr. Yai.

59
00:05:28,400 --> 00:05:30,480
Uh, Ms. Nee didn't recognize you.

60
00:05:30,560 --> 00:05:32,360
Please don't hold it against her.

61
00:05:32,920 --> 00:05:35,640
You're older than her,
so please forgive her.

62
00:05:39,360 --> 00:05:41,360
I've never bullied anyone first.

63
00:05:48,360 --> 00:05:49,680
- Here, Yai.
- Yeah, come on.

64
00:05:50,240 --> 00:05:51,840
Yeah, eat up.

65
00:05:51,920 --> 00:05:53,360
- Yeah.
- Open up. Yeah.

66
00:05:53,440 --> 00:05:54,680
Yeah. Come at me.

67
00:05:55,200 --> 00:05:56,880
- Open. Yeah.
- Yeah.

68
00:05:56,960 --> 00:05:58,640
Yummy, huh?

69
00:05:59,400 --> 00:06:01,720
- Hey, that's enough.
- Just eat it.

70
00:06:01,800 --> 00:06:02,880
My fart would stink.

71
00:06:03,880 --> 00:06:05,000
Here, take this.

72
00:06:06,040 --> 00:06:07,040
Come on.

73
00:06:07,560 --> 00:06:09,480
It's a sandwich. Here.

74
00:06:13,680 --> 00:06:16,640
What's in this? It smells like dog poop.

75
00:06:47,240 --> 00:06:48,480
What's wrong?

76
00:06:49,160 --> 00:06:51,120
Yai is pranking me.

77
00:06:51,200 --> 00:06:55,720
There's a Blythe doll that Auntie
just bought for me in that backpack too.

78
00:06:56,320 --> 00:06:58,520
It's okay. I'll get it for you.

79
00:07:04,480 --> 00:07:06,000
She's gonna fall.

80
00:07:22,240 --> 00:07:23,640
My Blythe.

81
00:07:51,120 --> 00:07:54,040
Is that true, Noi? Is that really Mr. Yai?

82
00:07:54,120 --> 00:07:55,880
You're imagining things, aren't you?

83
00:07:55,960 --> 00:07:57,720
But Auntie…

84
00:07:57,800 --> 00:08:00,320
She told me Yai was dead.

85
00:08:02,720 --> 00:08:05,640
When Madam comes back,
you can ask her yourself.

86
00:08:15,920 --> 00:08:17,720
It's been a long time since that happened.

87
00:08:17,800 --> 00:08:19,640
Can't you forgive her?

88
00:08:19,720 --> 00:08:23,720
We need to move forward,
not dwell on past grievances.

89
00:08:26,520 --> 00:08:28,360
Thieves only have one rule.

90
00:08:31,800 --> 00:08:33,559
Kill first if you want to survive.

91
00:08:38,520 --> 00:08:41,760
Then I'll take the blame for her.

92
00:08:41,840 --> 00:08:43,640
Let it end here.

93
00:08:45,800 --> 00:08:48,560
You haven't changed at all. That's fine.

94
00:08:51,440 --> 00:08:52,400
Pin?

95
00:08:55,400 --> 00:08:56,520
Come here.

96
00:08:57,720 --> 00:08:59,320
Get in. Sit still.

97
00:09:29,920 --> 00:09:31,040
Pin.

98
00:09:31,720 --> 00:09:32,840
Yes?

99
00:09:32,920 --> 00:09:35,560
Won't you explain anything to me
or show me around?

100
00:09:38,240 --> 00:09:40,000
What would you like to know?

101
00:09:41,080 --> 00:09:42,440
Well…

102
00:09:42,520 --> 00:09:44,840
let's pretend I'm a tourist.

103
00:10:01,760 --> 00:10:05,360
This area is an exotic animal exhibit.

104
00:10:05,880 --> 00:10:09,320
On weekends and holidays,
tourists can purchase tickets to enter,

105
00:10:10,680 --> 00:10:12,320
take photos, and feed the animals.

106
00:10:13,800 --> 00:10:18,720
But if you're staying in the resort,
you can visit for free.

107
00:10:29,640 --> 00:10:31,720
And you? It's been so long.

108
00:10:31,800 --> 00:10:32,640
How have you been doing?

109
00:10:49,800 --> 00:10:53,200
Ah! Mr. Yai, please drive more carefully.

110
00:10:53,280 --> 00:10:54,760
Oh, you want something more thrilling?

111
00:10:54,840 --> 00:10:56,480
Sure, you got it.

112
00:10:56,560 --> 00:10:57,760
- Mr. Yai.
- Whoo!

113
00:10:57,840 --> 00:11:00,480
- Mr. Yai.
- Whoa.

114
00:11:00,560 --> 00:11:02,680
- Careful.
- Whoo!

115
00:11:02,760 --> 00:11:04,200
Watch out, Mr. Yai!

116
00:11:06,480 --> 00:11:07,520
Pin!

117
00:11:12,200 --> 00:11:13,240
Are you hurt?

118
00:11:13,760 --> 00:11:15,720
You screamed so loud, it startled me.

119
00:11:19,160 --> 00:11:22,200
You too. Don't you know
how to use a crosswalk?

120
00:11:22,280 --> 00:11:24,480
Do you not wanna live
to be a hundred years old?

121
00:11:24,560 --> 00:11:25,600
Fine.

122
00:11:25,680 --> 00:11:27,000
Mr. Yai, please don't.

123
00:11:27,600 --> 00:11:30,080
Come on. You feel sorry
for all the animals in the world?

124
00:11:30,160 --> 00:11:32,280
Don't you remember Tuem, Mr. Yai?

125
00:11:48,000 --> 00:11:49,600
Tuem must have gotten out.

126
00:11:50,200 --> 00:11:52,920
You like to travel a lot, huh?

127
00:11:55,560 --> 00:11:59,400
Ever since you weren't around,
he has been wandering all over the farm.

128
00:11:59,480 --> 00:12:02,080
I felt sorry for him,
so I decided to take care of him myself.

129
00:12:02,960 --> 00:12:06,680
I never thought that
he would become this huge.

130
00:12:07,360 --> 00:12:08,240
Hmm?

131
00:12:08,960 --> 00:12:10,000
Well, Tuem?

132
00:12:10,640 --> 00:12:12,600
Remember your owner?

133
00:12:31,640 --> 00:12:32,520
Thank you, Pin.

134
00:12:33,640 --> 00:12:35,440
I'm getting tired of dog meat.

135
00:12:36,200 --> 00:12:39,520
Imagine if I turned his meat into
a spicy salad, drizzled with sour lime

136
00:12:39,600 --> 00:12:43,600
and packed with garden chilis
just to feel that burn in my nose…

137
00:12:45,080 --> 00:12:47,160
Right, Tuem?

138
00:12:48,160 --> 00:12:50,080
I can't believe

139
00:12:50,160 --> 00:12:53,680
you've turned into a cruel
and heartless man like this.

140
00:12:56,360 --> 00:13:00,880
You think a fugitive murderer like me
would adore children, women, the elderly?

141
00:13:01,400 --> 00:13:03,920
You must spend a lot of time
with sheep and goats, Pinanong.

142
00:13:04,600 --> 00:13:07,200
Yes, I spend time with animals.

143
00:13:07,280 --> 00:13:09,440
So I know that animals have souls,

144
00:13:09,520 --> 00:13:13,320
treasure their lives just like we do,
and feel pain too.

145
00:13:13,400 --> 00:13:15,120
You think you can eat anything?

146
00:13:15,200 --> 00:13:17,520
Why don't you
cut your own flesh and eat it?

147
00:13:20,200 --> 00:13:21,280
Okay.

148
00:13:24,680 --> 00:13:25,920
I've changed my mind.

149
00:13:27,400 --> 00:13:30,000
I think I'll go back and butcher Tatsanee.

150
00:13:30,640 --> 00:13:32,360
Let's finish unresolved business.

151
00:13:35,840 --> 00:13:38,760
Mr. Yai. Mr. Yai. Mr. Yai!

152
00:13:39,720 --> 00:13:40,880
Mr. Yai, wait!

153
00:13:43,920 --> 00:13:45,040
Mr. Yai.

154
00:13:46,800 --> 00:13:47,920
Mr. Yai…

155
00:14:16,320 --> 00:14:18,280
- Pull up right here!
- Ah!

156
00:14:20,240 --> 00:14:21,080
What is it?

157
00:14:21,680 --> 00:14:25,000
I think this view looks familiar.

158
00:14:47,000 --> 00:14:48,680
What's this tree again?

159
00:14:54,120 --> 00:14:55,360
It's an Indian cork tree.

160
00:15:02,640 --> 00:15:04,200
Grow up quickly, my Indian cork.

161
00:15:04,280 --> 00:15:06,520
You represent Mr. Na,

162
00:15:06,600 --> 00:15:09,720
the boy who's the kindest
and nicest to me.

163
00:15:20,160 --> 00:15:22,560
Mr. Yai.

164
00:15:22,640 --> 00:15:24,040
What are you doing, Mr. Yai?

165
00:15:26,040 --> 00:15:28,880
Please don't, Mr. Yai. Don't do it.

166
00:15:28,960 --> 00:15:30,080
Don't do that.

167
00:15:34,720 --> 00:15:38,360
Indian cork… Please stay with me.

168
00:15:39,120 --> 00:15:40,760
Please don't die.

169
00:15:44,120 --> 00:15:45,800
It managed to survive, huh?

170
00:15:46,400 --> 00:15:49,760
You must have high regard
for the person who gave it to you.

171
00:15:50,520 --> 00:15:53,200
But I think this tree
is a bit of a nuisance,

172
00:15:53,280 --> 00:15:55,800
blocking the beautiful view.

173
00:15:56,760 --> 00:15:58,600
Tourists probably won't like it.

174
00:16:15,480 --> 00:16:16,800
What are you doing, Mr. Yai?

175
00:16:18,640 --> 00:16:20,680
I'm going to cut down
this tree, obviously.

176
00:16:20,760 --> 00:16:22,760
If you dare to swing
that axe at me, just do it.

177
00:16:23,520 --> 00:16:24,680
What do you want from me?

178
00:16:25,200 --> 00:16:26,680
I can't kill the tortoise.

179
00:16:26,760 --> 00:16:28,280
I can't teach Nee a lesson.

180
00:16:28,360 --> 00:16:29,880
And I can't even cut down a tree!

181
00:16:30,520 --> 00:16:31,400
Move!

182
00:16:33,080 --> 00:16:36,200
You're mistaken if you think

183
00:16:36,280 --> 00:16:37,920
I'm soft-hearted with women, girly.

184
00:16:38,520 --> 00:16:39,960
I've spent a long time nurturing it.

185
00:16:42,080 --> 00:16:44,920
It's my love and my memory.

186
00:16:48,480 --> 00:16:51,240
A maid with no future like me

187
00:16:51,320 --> 00:16:54,560
can only find a shred of happiness
in watching this tree grow.

188
00:17:29,440 --> 00:17:30,440
Hey, stop.

189
00:17:32,200 --> 00:17:34,920
- Mr. Yai! Pin, help me.
- I said stop.

190
00:17:35,000 --> 00:17:36,160
Pin.

191
00:17:39,920 --> 00:17:44,160
Mr. Yai suddenly punched me
and accused me of taking Uncle from him.

192
00:17:45,840 --> 00:17:47,160
You're bleeding, Mr. Na.

193
00:17:47,800 --> 00:17:50,160
That's a lie. And that's just a nosebleed.

194
00:17:50,240 --> 00:17:51,680
He's blaming me for it.

195
00:17:52,800 --> 00:17:54,200
Don't hurt Mr. Na.

196
00:17:54,720 --> 00:17:57,040
If you like picking on the weak, go ahead.

197
00:17:58,520 --> 00:17:59,680
Stop right there, Yai.

198
00:18:05,120 --> 00:18:07,960
Who taught you to bully girls? Huh?

199
00:18:45,440 --> 00:18:47,120
<i>Come back here right now, Yai.</i>

200
00:18:47,200 --> 00:18:50,680
<i>If you cause any more trouble,</i>
<i>I won't clean up after you.</i>

201
00:18:51,200 --> 00:18:52,680
<i>I won't even go pick up your corpse.</i>

202
00:18:55,000 --> 00:18:57,120
Yeah, I won't die easily.

203
00:18:57,640 --> 00:18:59,120
I'll be in touch.

204
00:19:13,480 --> 00:19:15,040
Where do you think you're going?

205
00:19:17,160 --> 00:19:20,480
I'd rather face the unknown
than wait for Yai to butcher me.

206
00:19:21,200 --> 00:19:22,960
I won't let you go.

207
00:19:26,040 --> 00:19:27,560
Why would you care, Auntie?

208
00:19:27,640 --> 00:19:30,840
You never even bothered to see
whether I was dead or alive.

209
00:19:30,920 --> 00:19:34,640
You should be happy
I've decided to go, Auntie.

210
00:19:42,360 --> 00:19:44,080
It hurts, Auntie!

211
00:19:45,400 --> 00:19:49,960
How many times did you and your filthy men
scheme to extort money from me?

212
00:19:50,040 --> 00:19:52,880
You must stay and repay my kindness.

213
00:19:55,600 --> 00:19:56,720
Ugh!

214
00:20:08,120 --> 00:20:09,160
What's this, Auntie?

215
00:20:10,080 --> 00:20:13,320
Use your femininity to your advantage.

216
00:20:13,400 --> 00:20:15,720
Don't be foolish,
wasting both money and your body.

217
00:20:16,480 --> 00:20:21,600
Do what I say, and you'll get everything
that belonged to that old man Paisan.

218
00:20:22,560 --> 00:20:23,880
Do you want that or not?

219
00:20:34,200 --> 00:20:35,400
Is it really going to work?

220
00:20:35,480 --> 00:20:37,000
Have you put too much on the line?

221
00:20:37,800 --> 00:20:39,640
No matter how tough he is,

222
00:20:39,720 --> 00:20:42,040
he'll lose it
when it comes to bedroom stuff.

223
00:20:42,120 --> 00:20:43,200
He won't be able to resist.

224
00:20:49,240 --> 00:20:50,400
Just like I did, right?

225
00:20:53,040 --> 00:20:54,680
Someone might see us.

226
00:20:55,520 --> 00:20:57,120
I'll poke their eyes blind.

227
00:21:29,280 --> 00:21:30,400
What is it?

228
00:21:30,480 --> 00:21:34,520
<i>Boss, I just saw</i>
<i>Yai check into a room at the resort.</i>

229
00:21:35,440 --> 00:21:39,160
But he pretended to be a tourist.
I thought it was a bit strange,

230
00:21:39,800 --> 00:21:41,280
so I called to let you know.

231
00:21:41,360 --> 00:21:42,440
Mm.

232
00:21:44,920 --> 00:21:46,400
Yai's at the resort now.

233
00:21:46,480 --> 00:21:48,280
Do you think he's investigating something?

234
00:21:51,280 --> 00:21:52,320
Let him be.

235
00:21:52,840 --> 00:21:54,520
The opportunity has come to us.

236
00:22:00,560 --> 00:22:03,520
Nee, listen to me carefully.

237
00:22:09,200 --> 00:22:12,160
Your mom borrowed my phone
to call the farm.

238
00:22:12,240 --> 00:22:15,600
After talking to them,
she rushed back there immediately.

239
00:22:16,200 --> 00:22:19,040
I told her to wait for you,
but she wouldn't listen.

240
00:22:22,480 --> 00:22:25,520
I told you
not to open that cabin to guests.

241
00:22:25,600 --> 00:22:27,600
We are down to a single maid right now.

242
00:22:27,680 --> 00:22:31,560
If guests complain on social media,
our resort's reputation will be ruined.

243
00:22:32,080 --> 00:22:35,360
But Madam told me to welcome every guest.

244
00:22:35,880 --> 00:22:37,920
She said money is our top priority.

245
00:22:38,480 --> 00:22:41,560
Also, that man looks like he's hungover.

246
00:22:41,640 --> 00:22:44,600
Maybe he can't even think straight,
let alone post on social media.

247
00:22:45,200 --> 00:22:48,320
Oh, my. Are you sure
he's not a crook or a psychopath?

248
00:22:48,400 --> 00:22:51,040
Will he be able to pay?

249
00:22:51,960 --> 00:22:53,480
Why wouldn't he?

250
00:22:59,440 --> 00:23:02,480
Don't you know he's Mr. Yai,

251
00:23:03,400 --> 00:23:06,160
the real owner of Paisan Farm?

252
00:23:07,080 --> 00:23:08,160
Huh?

253
00:23:09,000 --> 00:23:10,160
The farm owner?

254
00:23:47,760 --> 00:23:48,760
Is this

255
00:23:49,560 --> 00:23:51,880
really Mr. Paisan's dream resort?

256
00:25:17,880 --> 00:25:20,040
Are you in here?

257
00:25:27,080 --> 00:25:28,320
Where is he?

258
00:25:32,840 --> 00:25:35,520
Oh. I thought it was someone else.

259
00:25:35,600 --> 00:25:37,040
It's Nee… I mean,

260
00:25:38,000 --> 00:25:40,120
my lady.

261
00:25:41,560 --> 00:25:42,640
Oh.

262
00:25:42,720 --> 00:25:46,600
Mr. Yai, I must apologize

263
00:25:46,680 --> 00:25:50,280
for offending you
by assuming you were just a worker.

264
00:25:50,360 --> 00:25:53,520
I've made an unforgivable mistake.

265
00:25:54,040 --> 00:25:57,320
So, I'm willing to accept

266
00:25:57,400 --> 00:26:01,280
whatever punishment you decide, Mr. Yai.

267
00:26:01,360 --> 00:26:03,320
Oh…

268
00:26:03,400 --> 00:26:05,400
Don't be so serious about that.

269
00:26:05,480 --> 00:26:07,280
We were just joking around.

270
00:26:07,360 --> 00:26:09,440
That's perfectly normal.

271
00:26:09,520 --> 00:26:13,120
Who would be so cruel
as to punish my little sister?

272
00:26:13,200 --> 00:26:15,720
Come here, let me kiss your forehead.

273
00:26:20,440 --> 00:26:22,160
Oh. Oh, wow.

274
00:26:23,640 --> 00:26:25,800
Is this herbal tea?

275
00:26:28,040 --> 00:26:29,840
Yes, it is!

276
00:26:30,440 --> 00:26:32,720
I knew you'd like it.

277
00:26:32,800 --> 00:26:38,040
So I carefully brewed this fragrant
and silky tea specifically for you.

278
00:26:38,120 --> 00:26:39,800
I'm sure you'll love it.

279
00:26:42,120 --> 00:26:43,520
If it's as delicate as you said,

280
00:26:43,600 --> 00:26:46,200
I'll give you a nice reward.

281
00:27:20,280 --> 00:27:21,480
- Noi.
- Ah!

282
00:27:21,560 --> 00:27:23,840
Oh, I'm sorry. Aunt Un?

283
00:27:23,920 --> 00:27:25,600
- What?
- Why are you here?

284
00:27:26,440 --> 00:27:28,640
You said Mr. Yai came back.

285
00:27:29,280 --> 00:27:31,120
How could I just
lie in bed and do nothing?

286
00:27:31,680 --> 00:27:34,400
So, where's Mr. Yai now?

287
00:27:34,480 --> 00:27:36,920
- Huh?
- Here's the thing, Aunt Un.

288
00:27:39,320 --> 00:27:40,160
Un.

289
00:27:42,080 --> 00:27:42,920
Madam.

290
00:27:43,520 --> 00:27:44,520
Oh.

291
00:27:48,520 --> 00:27:51,120
Are you feeling better now?

292
00:27:51,720 --> 00:27:55,200
I was so worried about you,
I couldn't eat or sleep.

293
00:27:55,280 --> 00:27:56,360
- Oh…
- Mm.

294
00:27:56,440 --> 00:27:59,640
But I couldn't visit you

295
00:28:00,280 --> 00:28:02,240
because the farm was facing disaster.

296
00:28:04,760 --> 00:28:06,520
I've heard about it, Madam.

297
00:28:07,120 --> 00:28:08,760
I was told about Mr. Yai too.

298
00:28:08,840 --> 00:28:11,600
Did he do anything to you, Madam?

299
00:28:12,160 --> 00:28:13,560
Are you okay?

300
00:28:15,480 --> 00:28:18,560
Keep it down. We can't talk here.

301
00:28:29,080 --> 00:28:31,840
- Valued customer.
- Yes?

302
00:28:31,920 --> 00:28:33,240
Valued customer.

303
00:28:33,320 --> 00:28:35,120
Please lie down, sir.

304
00:28:35,200 --> 00:28:36,520
This therapist will step on…

305
00:28:36,600 --> 00:28:37,600
- Hmm?
- Oh, I mean

306
00:28:38,440 --> 00:28:40,320
I'll massage you.

307
00:28:40,400 --> 00:28:41,840
Oh.

308
00:28:57,000 --> 00:28:59,280
Where are you going, huh?

309
00:29:06,600 --> 00:29:08,600
Wait, wait. Hold on.

310
00:29:08,680 --> 00:29:10,480
Careful, that's a sensitive spot.

311
00:29:11,080 --> 00:29:12,720
That's a sensitive spot?

312
00:29:16,520 --> 00:29:18,880
What about right here?

313
00:29:20,160 --> 00:29:21,440
Even more sensitive.

314
00:29:21,520 --> 00:29:25,120
- It's even more sensitive?
- Ooh.

315
00:29:25,200 --> 00:29:27,200
What about here?

316
00:29:27,280 --> 00:29:30,920
Oh, wow. It tickles here.

317
00:29:37,720 --> 00:29:39,360
Oh, whoa. Stop it!

318
00:29:39,880 --> 00:29:42,080
You're provoking a big fierce tiger.

319
00:29:42,160 --> 00:29:43,840
You'll be punished for this.

320
00:29:49,160 --> 00:29:50,360
Little doe,

321
00:29:50,880 --> 00:29:52,800
your meat must be sweet and fragrant.

322
00:29:52,880 --> 00:29:54,800
Let me taste it.

323
00:30:13,520 --> 00:30:16,600
Come, let me taste it.

324
00:30:47,440 --> 00:30:50,760
Mr. Yai. Mr. Yai, don't do this.

325
00:30:50,840 --> 00:30:52,240
Uh, please don't, Mr. Yai.

326
00:30:52,320 --> 00:30:53,760
Don't do this to me.

327
00:30:55,560 --> 00:30:56,640
Good.

328
00:30:57,440 --> 00:31:01,520
Make him infatuated with you,
then find a way to get rid of him.

329
00:31:02,480 --> 00:31:04,400
You'll get even more than this after that.

330
00:31:06,240 --> 00:31:07,240
BANGKOK BANK

331
00:31:08,800 --> 00:31:11,600
I wouldn't sleep with you in any lifetime.

332
00:31:11,680 --> 00:31:13,800
Once I get paid, I'm gone.

333
00:31:16,720 --> 00:31:17,880
‪What?

334
00:31:22,040 --> 00:31:22,960
Where did he go?

335
00:31:23,720 --> 00:31:25,080
- Peekaboo!
- Ah!

336
00:31:25,960 --> 00:31:28,240
Mr. Yai! Why aren't you asleep?!

337
00:31:29,560 --> 00:31:32,080
Don't provoke a sleeping tiger
or awaken one.

338
00:31:32,160 --> 00:31:34,840
This big tiger has awakened,
more powerful than ever.

339
00:32:04,080 --> 00:32:06,760
Is he really that vile, Madam?

340
00:32:08,480 --> 00:32:10,240
Considering how bad he was as a kid,

341
00:32:10,960 --> 00:32:12,840
he's a hundred times worse now.

342
00:32:13,360 --> 00:32:17,200
That's why I didn't dare to confront him
directly, fearing he would kill me.

343
00:32:18,840 --> 00:32:19,880
No, Madam.

344
00:32:20,440 --> 00:32:23,520
If he tries that,
it will be over my dead body.

345
00:32:27,880 --> 00:32:29,760
Aside from my parents,

346
00:32:30,640 --> 00:32:33,280
you are the person who loves me the most.

347
00:32:38,840 --> 00:32:39,840
Oh, Un.

348
00:32:39,920 --> 00:32:42,120
Why are you suddenly bowing to me?

349
00:32:42,960 --> 00:32:44,000
Madam.

350
00:32:45,360 --> 00:32:48,640
I'm the one who should be grateful to you

351
00:32:49,760 --> 00:32:54,200
for taking care
of my surgery and hospital expenses.

352
00:32:54,280 --> 00:32:56,720
I will never forget
your kindness in this lifetime.

353
00:32:57,320 --> 00:32:58,520
Hospital expenses?

354
00:33:00,280 --> 00:33:04,200
The surgery fee
you transferred to the hospital.

355
00:33:04,280 --> 00:33:05,400
Pin told me

356
00:33:06,280 --> 00:33:08,200
you paid for everything.

357
00:33:10,240 --> 00:33:12,440
Oh, that money.

358
00:33:13,480 --> 00:33:15,080
Pin asked to borrow it.

359
00:33:15,600 --> 00:33:18,760
Who would be so cruel to refuse?

360
00:33:20,720 --> 00:33:22,000
Come here.

361
00:33:26,880 --> 00:33:28,560
You're like an older sister to me.

362
00:33:29,280 --> 00:33:32,200
Even if I have
to sacrifice myself to help you,

363
00:33:32,280 --> 00:33:33,800
I'll be willing to do it.

364
00:33:34,320 --> 00:33:35,640
Don't overthink it.

365
00:33:40,000 --> 00:33:41,240
Yes, Madam.

366
00:33:42,560 --> 00:33:43,800
Thank you so much.

367
00:34:06,360 --> 00:34:08,199
Aunt Juk, why aren't you being careful?

368
00:34:08,280 --> 00:34:10,800
Pin, hurry up and go the resort cabin.

369
00:34:11,480 --> 00:34:13,719
A guest is assaulting a woman.

370
00:34:13,800 --> 00:34:15,840
I heard her screams.

371
00:34:23,840 --> 00:34:24,760
Open the door!

372
00:34:26,480 --> 00:34:29,280
Open the door right now,
or I'll call the police.

373
00:34:30,080 --> 00:34:31,159
Open the door!

374
00:34:32,400 --> 00:34:33,280
Call security.

375
00:34:33,360 --> 00:34:35,960
Security? Uh, he's on sick leave.

376
00:34:37,040 --> 00:34:38,880
- Then go get Jom.
- Okay.

377
00:34:38,960 --> 00:34:40,800
- Hurry.
- Jom. Jom.

378
00:34:41,360 --> 00:34:42,280
Open the door!

379
00:34:44,199 --> 00:34:45,320
Open the door!

380
00:34:51,360 --> 00:34:52,320
Mr. Yai?

381
00:34:52,920 --> 00:34:54,159
What are you doing here?

382
00:34:54,239 --> 00:34:55,760
And why did that woman scream?

383
00:34:55,840 --> 00:34:56,760
Mr. Yai!

384
00:34:57,720 --> 00:34:58,760
Ms. Nee?

385
00:34:59,520 --> 00:35:01,920
Mr. Yai, what did you do to her?

386
00:35:02,000 --> 00:35:03,440
Why did you lock her up?

387
00:35:04,360 --> 00:35:05,360
Ms. Nee.

388
00:35:30,880 --> 00:35:34,080
Mr. Yai! Open the door right now!

389
00:35:34,160 --> 00:35:36,240
Mr. Yai! Help me! Mr. Yai!

390
00:35:37,080 --> 00:35:40,280
Ms. Nee. Ms. Nee.

391
00:35:40,960 --> 00:35:43,160
Ms. Nee. Please open the door.

392
00:35:49,760 --> 00:35:51,200
Why isn't it working?!

393
00:35:58,760 --> 00:36:00,680
Mr. Yai! Open up!

394
00:36:01,520 --> 00:36:04,520
- Ms. Nee.
- You can't open it. The door's stuck.

395
00:36:04,600 --> 00:36:06,320
Could you please come help?

396
00:36:08,560 --> 00:36:09,680
My hands are full.

397
00:36:09,760 --> 00:36:10,760
I'm scratching here, alright?

398
00:36:11,800 --> 00:36:12,640
There are a lot of mosquitoes.

399
00:36:12,720 --> 00:36:15,200
The door's open,
so there are hundreds of them.

400
00:36:25,240 --> 00:36:26,320
Ms. Nee.

401
00:36:28,800 --> 00:36:31,040
I told you it can't be opened.

402
00:36:32,320 --> 00:36:34,200
Go! Get away from me!

403
00:36:34,760 --> 00:36:37,720
Ms. Nee. What's happening in there?!

404
00:36:40,040 --> 00:36:42,680
Ms. Nee! Hang in there.

405
00:36:49,040 --> 00:36:49,960
Ms. Nee.

406
00:36:52,280 --> 00:36:53,600
Ms. Nee.

407
00:36:53,680 --> 00:36:55,200
Please stop splashing water at them.

408
00:36:55,280 --> 00:36:57,240
They'll get scared. Ms. Nee.

409
00:37:02,480 --> 00:37:03,600
Ms. Nee.

410
00:37:18,000 --> 00:37:19,280
The hell am I doing here?

411
00:37:23,240 --> 00:37:24,280
Ugh.

412
00:38:06,880 --> 00:38:08,520
Hey, who's that?

413
00:38:09,760 --> 00:38:10,760
Hey.

414
00:38:11,600 --> 00:38:14,200
Hey! Stop right there! Hey!

415
00:38:38,480 --> 00:38:41,000
Help! Help!

416
00:38:41,920 --> 00:38:44,920
A thief! There's a thief in the car! Help!

417
00:38:45,840 --> 00:38:48,320
Hey! Hey, stop running!

418
00:38:48,840 --> 00:38:49,760
Hey!

419
00:39:04,800 --> 00:39:05,880
I'll just hide here.

420
00:39:09,880 --> 00:39:10,840
Don't be afraid.

421
00:39:10,920 --> 00:39:11,840
I'm just hiding for a bit.

422
00:39:14,080 --> 00:39:15,080
Hey.

423
00:39:15,160 --> 00:39:16,120
Ah.

424
00:39:16,760 --> 00:39:19,320
Do you believe now
that I didn't do anything to Nee?

425
00:39:20,920 --> 00:39:22,880
The housekeeper must have misunderstood.

426
00:39:23,520 --> 00:39:27,040
I'm sorry for my poor choice of words.

427
00:39:27,120 --> 00:39:28,200
It's okay.

428
00:39:28,840 --> 00:39:30,960
Sin is like ink on skin.

429
00:39:31,040 --> 00:39:32,400
Once it's there, it's permanent.

430
00:39:33,520 --> 00:39:36,400
So, how did Ms. Nee end up
being in there with you?

431
00:39:37,800 --> 00:39:39,680
Nee served me this herbal tea,

432
00:39:40,280 --> 00:39:42,120
intending to drug me
and do something to me.

433
00:39:45,400 --> 00:39:47,960
Ms. Nee? Drug you?

434
00:39:58,440 --> 00:40:00,520
I drank it too quickly
and almost choked on it.

435
00:40:04,480 --> 00:40:05,680
Whoa.

436
00:40:05,760 --> 00:40:07,160
Bottoms up, huh?

437
00:40:08,480 --> 00:40:11,640
But you shouldn't have
teased her like that.

438
00:40:11,720 --> 00:40:13,680
She's terrified of reptiles.

439
00:40:13,760 --> 00:40:15,080
You know that.

440
00:40:15,160 --> 00:40:17,000
She might go into shock,
just as she did years ago.

441
00:40:17,080 --> 00:40:18,080
What?

442
00:40:18,160 --> 00:40:20,360
And what if I ended up
sleeping with that vixen?

443
00:40:20,440 --> 00:40:21,880
It's my loss.

444
00:40:25,160 --> 00:40:29,680
A man shouldn't be sexually harassed
by a woman either, right?

445
00:40:29,760 --> 00:40:31,760
Ms. Nee wouldn't do anything like that.

446
00:40:31,840 --> 00:40:33,160
It doesn't make sense.

447
00:40:33,240 --> 00:40:34,680
Oh?

448
00:40:34,760 --> 00:40:37,880
Why not? I own this farm.

449
00:40:37,960 --> 00:40:40,080
Everyone would want me to be their in-law.

450
00:40:40,680 --> 00:40:42,520
You assume too much, Mr. Yai.

451
00:40:43,960 --> 00:40:45,520
Pin, where are you going?

452
00:40:45,600 --> 00:40:47,040
We haven't finished talking.

453
00:40:47,120 --> 00:40:49,080
I'm going to check on my mom.

454
00:40:49,160 --> 00:40:51,200
The hospital said she's back home now.

455
00:40:51,280 --> 00:40:52,520
I don't know how she's doing.

456
00:40:52,600 --> 00:40:54,520
Ow! Ouch!

457
00:40:54,600 --> 00:40:57,040
Mr. Yai, what's wrong, Mr. Yai?

458
00:40:57,120 --> 00:41:00,600
Oh, my heart is pounding so hard that
it feels like it's about to burst.

459
00:41:00,680 --> 00:41:01,680
It must have been Nee.

460
00:41:01,760 --> 00:41:03,840
She must have added
too much sleeping medication.

461
00:41:04,360 --> 00:41:06,920
I spat it out,
but I can still feel the effects.

462
00:41:10,520 --> 00:41:11,680
Is your heart beating very fast?

463
00:41:12,280 --> 00:41:13,480
Should we go see a doctor?

464
00:41:14,240 --> 00:41:16,120
I can't tell. Why don't you listen to it?

465
00:41:16,200 --> 00:41:19,080
Hurry. Pin, hurry.

466
00:41:21,720 --> 00:41:23,400
I don't see how it's fast.

467
00:41:25,520 --> 00:41:26,760
It's beating like rock 'n' roll.

468
00:41:26,840 --> 00:41:27,720
Isn't it fast?

469
00:41:27,800 --> 00:41:30,200
Listen carefully. Pin, listen carefully.

470
00:41:37,560 --> 00:41:39,160
Are you playing with me?

471
00:41:39,240 --> 00:41:40,520
- That's not gentlemanly.
- Wait.

472
00:41:40,600 --> 00:41:42,800
Are you hitting your benefactor?

473
00:41:42,880 --> 00:41:45,240
I paid for your mom's medical bill.

474
00:41:45,320 --> 00:41:46,640
Don't you think you should thank me?

475
00:41:46,720 --> 00:41:47,920
Huh?

476
00:41:49,360 --> 00:41:52,080
What? That was your money, Mr. Yai?

477
00:41:53,360 --> 00:41:55,680
You think it fell from the sky?

478
00:41:56,280 --> 00:41:57,400
Remember.

479
00:41:57,480 --> 00:42:00,080
From now on, you're indebted to me,

480
00:42:00,160 --> 00:42:01,840
Puny Pin.

481
00:42:09,000 --> 00:42:12,840
You're young and good looking,
but you decided to become a thief?

482
00:42:12,920 --> 00:42:15,040
We need to let the world
see you and condemn you.

483
00:42:15,120 --> 00:42:16,080
Hey, don't do it.

484
00:42:16,680 --> 00:42:18,920
That's a violation of the PDPA.

485
00:42:19,520 --> 00:42:21,560
I can sue you for both civil
and criminal offenses.

486
00:42:21,640 --> 00:42:23,160
PAISAN

487
00:42:23,240 --> 00:42:26,360
Try it. If you want to stand alone
in front of the judges, go ahead.

488
00:42:27,360 --> 00:42:28,840
A smartass, huh?

489
00:42:29,960 --> 00:42:30,800
Who the hell are you?

490
00:42:30,880 --> 00:42:32,640
Why did you sneak into the farm?

491
00:42:33,560 --> 00:42:34,840
I'm lost.

492
00:42:36,640 --> 00:42:38,320
- You're lost?!
- Ouch.

493
00:42:38,400 --> 00:42:39,920
- Lost?!
- Stop!

494
00:42:40,720 --> 00:42:44,000
Assault, battery, and false imprisonment,
those are heavy charges.

495
00:42:45,960 --> 00:42:48,400
You're the one
who should be arrested for trespassing.

496
00:42:48,480 --> 00:42:49,960
Take him to the police.

497
00:42:50,720 --> 00:42:51,720
Hey, no.

498
00:42:51,800 --> 00:42:52,960
- I didn't trespass.
- Get up!

499
00:42:53,040 --> 00:42:54,120
- I'm lost.
- Stop it.

500
00:42:54,200 --> 00:42:55,080
I didn't trespass.

501
00:42:55,160 --> 00:42:56,280
What's happening, Win?

502
00:42:56,880 --> 00:42:58,480
This guy stole Ms. Nee's truck.

503
00:43:03,520 --> 00:43:04,800
Mr. Yai?

504
00:43:06,960 --> 00:43:09,000
Pan! It's you?

505
00:43:09,080 --> 00:43:10,720
Why the hell are you laughing?

506
00:43:10,800 --> 00:43:12,120
Tell them to let me go!

507
00:43:12,200 --> 00:43:13,560
You know him?

508
00:43:14,680 --> 00:43:15,880
We were supposed to meet yesterday.

509
00:43:15,960 --> 00:43:18,000
Why did you just show up? Move, move.

510
00:43:18,080 --> 00:43:20,000
Come here. Ugh.

511
00:43:30,920 --> 00:43:31,760
Oh.

512
00:43:31,840 --> 00:43:33,480
This is my bestie.

513
00:43:33,560 --> 00:43:35,600
It's Pan, Uncle Pload's son.

514
00:43:35,680 --> 00:43:36,840
Don't you remember, Win?

515
00:43:37,760 --> 00:43:39,480
You're Pload's son?

516
00:43:41,640 --> 00:43:43,560
Yes. I'm Pload's son.

517
00:43:44,840 --> 00:43:46,320
He's changed a lot, hasn't he?

518
00:43:46,400 --> 00:43:48,360
Because now he's Pan,

519
00:43:48,440 --> 00:43:50,440
the son of the great bandit Pload.

520
00:43:50,520 --> 00:43:54,600
People call him "Pan of Pa Wai,
the outlaw of the borderlands."

521
00:43:59,920 --> 00:44:01,920
The outlaw of the borderlands.

522
00:44:10,680 --> 00:44:12,880
<i>Babe, did you get the money yet?</i>

523
00:44:14,320 --> 00:44:16,200
Not yet, babe.

524
00:44:16,280 --> 00:44:17,360
Can you wait a little longer?

525
00:44:17,440 --> 00:44:19,280
I'll let you know when I get it.

526
00:44:23,800 --> 00:44:25,080
How was it?

527
00:44:25,160 --> 00:44:27,040
Why didn't you call me when you got back?

528
00:44:27,880 --> 00:44:30,280
I was about to, but you're here now.

529
00:44:31,080 --> 00:44:31,960
Did it work?

530
00:44:32,600 --> 00:44:34,160
Not even close.

531
00:44:34,720 --> 00:44:37,240
Yai is both sadistic and psychotic.

532
00:44:37,320 --> 00:44:39,840
He locked me in a room
crawling with geckos.

533
00:44:39,920 --> 00:44:42,120
A whole nest of geckos, Auntie.

534
00:44:42,720 --> 00:44:45,080
I don't want his goddamn money anymore.

535
00:44:50,120 --> 00:44:51,680
Pretentious brat!

536
00:44:52,200 --> 00:44:54,800
I knew you were no good.

537
00:44:54,880 --> 00:44:55,840
You're stupid.

538
00:44:55,920 --> 00:44:57,320
You've never accomplished anything.

539
00:44:57,400 --> 00:44:58,960
What a waste.

540
00:44:59,040 --> 00:45:00,760
You're nothing compared to your brother.

541
00:45:03,880 --> 00:45:08,520
Yes, I'm stupid. Big breasts, small brain.

542
00:45:08,600 --> 00:45:11,520
But I don't know where I got those from.

543
00:45:14,320 --> 00:45:15,360
Come here. Come here.

544
00:45:17,080 --> 00:45:18,480
What are you doing, Auntie?!

545
00:45:19,080 --> 00:45:21,400
I don't believe your crazy gecko story.

546
00:45:21,480 --> 00:45:24,840
- Go back to Yai right now.
- No, I'm not going back.

547
00:45:24,920 --> 00:45:26,000
Tatsanee!

548
00:45:26,520 --> 00:45:28,760
Don't think I can't cut you off.

549
00:45:29,320 --> 00:45:32,640
If having you around is useless,
I'd rather not have you around at all.

550
00:45:32,720 --> 00:45:36,080
And why don't you use Pin
to tempt Yai instead of me?

551
00:45:39,080 --> 00:45:40,880
What does Pin have to do with this?

552
00:45:41,920 --> 00:45:44,240
She ran in to help me all of a sudden.

553
00:45:44,320 --> 00:45:47,440
It's obvious that she's leading Yai on.

554
00:45:51,360 --> 00:45:55,440
<i>From now on, Bandit Pan will assist me</i>
<i>in running this farm.</i>

555
00:45:55,520 --> 00:45:56,720
<i>You okay with that, Auntie?</i>

556
00:45:56,800 --> 00:45:58,000
Mr. Yai!

557
00:46:02,560 --> 00:46:05,920
Swear to this statue Majesty
that you will never betray Madam

558
00:46:06,000 --> 00:46:09,120
by siding with
or helping Yai in harming her.

559
00:46:09,200 --> 00:46:13,440
Otherwise, all ties between us
will be severed from now on.

560
00:46:56,320 --> 00:46:58,520
Subtitle translation by: Anan Pratchayakul
